		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just had a few other ideas for the edge filler that I'll play around with when I get the chance.  Hot glue works, but it is still very flexible once it has cooled, unlike the very rigid plastic that makes up the rest of the socket.  I can think of a few other options that should cure much more solidly, I just need to figure out how to properly dye them without compromising the curing process.

		

